Sentinel: You better go straight to the Shadow Forest Road if you want to go to Klaipeda. {nl} It is dangerous in the deep woods so try to stay away if you can.
Man in hiding
Fi... Finally! Have the rescue arrived? {nl} What! It's just a kid? Hey, are Vubbes still outside?
Ughh ... Go away! Do not talk to me! We're going to get caught by the Vubbes! {nl} This is my place so get out of here!
What? Do not lie to me! Vubbe's odor is stinging my nose. What!! {nl} Hey, you don't fool adults! Go away! Do not come around near this barrel!
Fi... Finally! Have the rescue arrived? {nl} What! It's just a kid? What are you looking at? Close the lid and just go on your way! {nl}
But the paper you're holding.. It looks familiar? {nl} Let me see that! What are you doing? There's an adult speaking to you!
This!! It's mine?! I will never give it again!! {nl} It's not something you need, I'm gonna rip it apart!
Sheesh, that's lame..
This is the first sign after all goddesses have dissappeared.{nl}Maybe, out of all those people, one person may bring the goddesses back.
Soldier Blag
I warn you! {nl}Mosters are attacking so all citizens run way! {nl}By the way, how come those citizens are in the military zone?{nl}

Ah, so you are the revelator! I am sorry that I didn't recognize you.{nl}Monsters are attacking the supply base at the moment.{nl}I want to take some important rations out from the base.. Please help me!
It was silent not too long ago, but now they are coming in mass.{nl}What is happening?
I felt unsafe..{nl}But, I didn't expect that they will come in mass.
There is the 1st supply warehouse when you go straight up the road.{nl}Please take out some remaining supplies..Damn..
In case you may need it in the future, I wrote down who Sparnas is.{nl}You may not know, but I was a biologist 4 years ago.
Please pass this report to Luders. {nl}He is probably at the central supply base.
Officer Luders
Ah, you must be the rumored revelator. Nice to meet you.{nl}Is this Blag's report?{nl}
Hmm.. Is that so.{nl}They just destroyed the supplies and ran away.  Even if Chupacabras have wings, I am sure that they can't do something like this.{nl}
It is little less.{nl}I am sorry, but please bring us the Moody's report at the crooked roat at Amzina.
I feel safe since Luders is here.
Soldier York
Siaulambs are breaking the norms.{nl}I am in panic myself, so I don't know what to do.{nl}Luders will not stand this.. What should we do?
Do you think the problem would be resolved by just defeating Sparnas?
Due to you help, I think I can get myself together.{nl}But.. this kind of thing will happen again right? Then What should I do..
Sparnas? We don't have an answer for that.{nl}It just appears from the sky without any signs, destroys all supplies and just dissappears.{nl}I get a headache by just listening to it's cries.
The place I just told you is the 2nd supply warehouse. {nl}It is depressing to think about that these kind of things will be recurring in the fututre

Take it. I made a bait from the old grains from the supplies.{nl}I will lure the guy up there so you stand still here.{nl}Sparnas will definitely appear at the one of these two places. Do not miss it and destroy it for sure.{nl}
We may not get a second chance if we don't defeat it this time.{nl}They are not idiots.
I heard the sound of fighting so I came here in a hurry..Have you defeated it?{nl}I only spotted Siaulambs.{nl}Well done. You have performed a meritorious deed.
Adjutant Paulina
We should get back the stolen stuffs.{nl}We shouldn't call ourself soldiers if we just do nothing.{nl}
We should get back the stolen stuffs.{nl}We shouldn't call ourself soldiers if we just do nothing.{nl}
I feel so upset to endure all the time.{nl}Reinforcement should come soon.  What can we expect from imcompetent kingdom?
Adjutant Volda
You must be busy for other things so thank you so much.{nl}We can't just endure all the time. We plan to keep attack.
Secret Guardian
The goddess already forecasted this.{nl}All beings can not escape from forecasting.
Liaison Officer Niels
Hello.{nl}Have you seen an oldman who lost his way?{nl}His name is Jonas.{nl}
You haven't seen him.{nl}Where is he now then. He is in his dotage.
Jonas is the descendent of the family that has been protecting this royal tomb.{nl}He is a very important person for our lab team so please take good care of him.
Archivist Jonas
Record officer Jonas
It is good to hear that Jonas regained his conciousness. {nl}You are the person who lifted the light signal right? {nl}
Ahylas came after seeing the light.{nl}Meet him downstairs.
We haven't heard a news from Kepeck for a long time after sending him supplies.{nl}We don't have enough seach team so please help us.
Historian Beard
Always prepare for monsters' attacks.{nl}Especially, outside places like here.
Mercenary Mirta
I already warned you?{nl}Please be careful next time.
Historian Kepeck
Niels must have sent you.{nl}Well, if you are in a hurry, record it yourself and take it to Niels.
When you straight on the right road and cross the bridge, you will see the artifacts of the great king, Zachariel. {nl}Record them and take that to Niels.  He will understand.
So this is Kepeck's record.. Mercenary Mirta was looking for this.{nl}I am okay as long as I can confirm their safety. Thank you for your efforts.
Ahylas Jonas
With that stone that will unlock the seal, please go to the Broken Pillar Canyon.{nl}The disciples of Gustas will tell you how to unlock the seal in sequential orders.
You haven't heard yet?{nl}You should meet the disciple of Gustas in the Broken Pillar Canyon.{nl}It was created to accept only the chosen ones.
Disciple of Gustas
Have you unlocked the seal of Pagasa cliff?{nl}It will start now.
Words carved into a rock
Do not touch or push it.
I was waiting for you.{nl}The next seal is located on the way to Broken Sanctum.
You won't know how eagerly we have waited for this moment.{nl}We really wanted to meet you.
Gustas Jonas
So it's you. {nl}You are much more of a man compared to what I had imagined.
Soldier Alan
You are a new soldier right?.{nl}I received a patrolling order, but I guess you can go on behalf of me.
You are good.{nl}I don't want to go there due to a horrible memory.
I am about to remember something..
You know that we are dispatched here to destroy Gaigalas right?{nl}Hey newcomer.  Can you take this report to the commander Wallis?
Commander Wallis
How come you brought this report instead of Alan?{nl}Are you a newcomer?
I can return home after we defeat Gaigalas.{nl}Ah, I want to just go home.
Wallis is at Three Footsteps.
I don't care how good you are. You are new here.{nl}It is an order. Bring some juice from Kepa Raiders.
Guys these days, they don't have guts. {nl}I hope you bring a good influence to them.
I am sure we will win this battle.{nl}Why? Owls told us that they will help us.
Kepa Raiders are near Ianutis Falls.{nl}To defeat Gaigalas, we really need that.
Soldier Weisz
Hey you are taking a rest?{nl}Get some oil from Duckey at Lanvas Garden.
We will lure Gaigalas using Ducky oil.{nl}Hey newcomer, don't loaf around.
Today will be the last day for Gaigalas.{nl}Necomer, are you ready?
Next, we will get the leather of Cronewt that lives in Lanvas Garden.{nl}Move fast, soldier.
We will win for sure this time.{nl}Since the goddesses are helping us.
You are good for a newcomer.{nl}It's disordered here at the moment so you keep those ingredients for now.{nl}
While I am preparing for a battle, get to know with our soldiers.{nl}I will call you before we confront Gaigalas.
When we burn Ducky oil, then Gaigalas will appear after smelling the odor from it.{nl}Lanvas Garden will be the good place to burn the oirl.
My heart is pounding.{nl}I feel like my spirit is shaking.
Statue of old owl
There's no one in this forest. Why are you here?{nl}
Gaigalas?{nl}It will be difficult to defeat it without anything.
I saw many deaths here.{nl}I don't want to see anymore sacrifices.
I need the juice from Kepa Raiders and the leather from Cronewt.
Why do you have that?{nl}Please hand it to me.  I will make Fragment of Memory.
I will revive the memories of our sleeping colleagues with this Fragment of Memory.
It will be difficult to defeat it without Fragment of Memory.{nl}Please bring the horn of Infroholder.
Archaeologist Dezic
Technician Heinen
Engineer Heinen
Rolandas Jonas
Mercenary Glen
Vaidotas
The smell.. I think the purifying device in the mine is broken. {nl}We better repair it quickly. The people taken away might suffocate.

Do you know the legend Cunningham? {nl} It's a legend about the great demon sealed here in the Crystal Mine. {nl} For more details, there is a book about it in the miners lounge of 2nd Gallery so try reading it. {nl}

Anyway, my guess is that the demon has re-awakening and controlling the Vubbes. {nl} The dream the bishop had and the legends of Cunningham ... l feel maybe it's a sign of something huge that's about to happen. {nl}
Only the Goddess would know if it's hope or despair. {nl}
The purifier be fixed easily by anyone but it may be hard to find the parts. {nl} In that case, use the compass that I gave you. {nl}
Well then, I have some other things to do so I will meet you in the 3rd Gallery. {nl} I wish for your fortune of war in the name of the Goddess .
If you can't repair the purifier, use the compass I gave you. {nl}You'll be able to find a way.
Village Aunt
Did you come to save us ? Did you?
Village Girl
Mr. Juan
I feel mad whenever I see those Vubbes that ruined my hometown. {Nl} That's why I want to help people like you who fight againt the Vubbes.
I would have left already if this wasn't my hometown. {nl} Where on earth have all the Vubbes been hiding before they crawled out.
Pharmacist lady
Soldier Jays
Even if the world changes, I will never forget the Vubbes.
Soldier Edgar
Knight Commander Uska
Is this slate the evidence of salvation? {nl} It just looks like an old slate to me.
You better ask Master Bokor about this slate. {Nl} She lives at the end of Klaipeda Residential Area so go pay her a visit.
Use your time wisely. {nl} No one can know everything about one's own future.
I'm also curious about the girl who cracked the seal. {nl} This is not a seal that can easily be unsealed.
Miner's Village Mayor
Welcome. Aren't you our town's savior. {nl}
So this revelation is Goddess Laima and we have to collect all these for the Goddess to regain her powers? {nl} That is amazing.
Oh, please do not reveal the fact that the Revelator has been found unless absolutely necessary. {nl} It may only create confusion if the rumors spread.
I have not heard of anything else about the bishop's dream. {nl} Sorry, I can't be much of help.
Klaipeda Guard Captain
Go ahead to Klaipeda. {nl} Commander Uska is waiting for you in Klaipeda Central Plaza. {nl} I heard the bishop also had a dream about the Goddess...  And I think it has to do with it.
Klaipeda Guard
Thank you for making your way here. {nl} If there is this much still left even after sir Titas handled it himself, can you imagine how it was before?
Mercenary Tobi
Supply Officer
Thank you for your help. {nl} I think this is enough. {nl}
)} {nl} If you have time, please tell our troops to assemble.{nl} If you don't want to, you may just go ahead to Klaipeda.
Scout
Go back, it's dangerous. {nl} Kepas will soon be marching in.
Oh, you're the Revelator. {nl} Since it's some fate that we fought together, let me give you a scoop of good information.
Oh, you mentioned that we need to assemble right? {nl}Help me find the missing luggage and I'll go as soon as I can.
Isn't the luggage ready yet? {nl} I can't go back without it.
Thank you. You found it sooner than I expected. {nl}
If you follow the road to the north, you will find the search scout. {nl} Well then, good luck.
Raimonas
Have you ever offered worship to the Statue? {nl} If not, I'd really recommend you to.
That depends on which Goddess it is. {nl} Go straight along way on the right.{nl} That's where Statue of Goddess Zemyna is so feel her blessings yourself.
I do worry that the monsters might harm the Statue of the Goddess.
Good thing to hear that the Statue is fine. {nl} The monsters should know that they should be afraid of the Goddess. {nl}
Go down the Shadow Forest Road and you should arrive at Klaipeda shortly. {nl} Well then, may be blessings of Goddess be with you
Plese do me a favor if you are headed to Klaipeda. {nl} It's not easy to go back and forth Kalipeda because of the Infro Rocktors nowadays.
Maybe taking care of the Statues will make the Goddesses return sooner...
Follow the road on the left of the camp crossroads. {nl}{-scp SCR_DIALOG_NPC_ANIM(
)}You'll meet the troops right away.
)}Alright, good job.{nl}You'll arrive at Klaipeda shortly when you follow the Shadow Forest Road.{nl}Don't forget to drop by Sir Uska.
Battle Commander
I will have my men notify the troops to assemble. {nl} You may return to sir Titas and let him know.
It's nothing difficult. {nl} If you don't want, I'll let you go to Kalipeda right away.
Search Scout
It sure is a problem. {nl} I didn't know Kepas could grow that big.
Shouldn't Revelators go to Klaipeda instead of here?
I feel so relieved to be positioned in the Western Woods. {nl} There are some places where you'd rather die than be positioned there.
When you see a Statue of Goddess, try offering a worship. {nl} Surely, something nice will happen.
This is a dangerous area. What are you doing here?
Thank you for your help. {nl} The Large Kepa appearing here.. Must report to Titas about it.
Weird.. That is not a type of monster you'd face in a place like this. {nl} It must be hard to just walk around
Assemble already? {nl} That's tough. There's still a pile of missions.
Please kill the Hanamings roaming around. {nl} And collect the flowers of Hanaming while you're at it.
Even if the Goddess arrived, I will not go until the mission is completed.
Yes. This should be enough. {nl} This is a pill that will restore your stamina instantly... I have enough of it so I will give you this as a gift. {nl}

Stamina is consumed when you move. {nl}You can recover stamina by destroying Tree Root Crystal or when you are in rest mode. {nl} But you don't have time for that when you are chased by monsters isn't it? {nl} And that's when this pill comes in handy.
I heard the news from my men and was starting to become worried. {nl} All is well if it ended up good.
Klaipeda Resident
)} {nl} When do you think the Goddess is coming back? {nl} Even if I ask the Revelators, all they say is that they must go to Klaipeda..
Are you the Revelator? {nl} You said the Goddess appeared in your dream. {nl}It's what the soldiers were saying.
Trooper
I wonder where and what the Goddess is doing...
Thank you for making your way until here. {nl}I am Uska, the Knight-Commander in charge of Siaulai and Klaipeda.
The bishop also dreamed of revelation. {nl} He said send the revelator to the Crystal Mine. {nl}
Let me know when you are ready to go to the Crystal Mine. {nl} I'll tell you the location and how to get into the Crystal Mine.
The Bishope told us to send the Revelator to Crystal Mine. {nl} He said the Goddess told him to do so. {nl}
But the Miner's Village is at war with the Vubbes {nl}and entrance is limited to authorized people only. {nl} Aras is the one in charge of Eastern Woods so try talking to him
Monsters have been around for long but they started becoming violent four years ago. {nl} The one that was affected the most would be plant types.{nl} They did not exist before. {nl}
Of course, beasts were no exception. {nl} When the monster that seemed like a fusion of the demon appeared, I thought it was all over.
Knight Aras
Aren't you hurt? {nl} Thank you for getting rid of the Poatas but you're so reckless.
You want to get into the Crystal Mine? {nl} The Miner's Village is currently at war with the Vubbes and it's very dangerous {nl}so I cannot permit that.
And our troops are in no condition to guard you. {nl} I'm sorry but you have to go back.
If you can't get rid of the Pokubus, you'll have to give up going into the Miner's Village.
Thank you. {nl} Do not worry, I'll keep my promise.
Outpost Sentinel
The Village is a problem but we also haven't had a rest because of the continuous battle.{nl}It will be much better if you can get rid of those Chupacabras.
Other monsters also show up when there are Chupacabras. {nl} Miner's Village is a problem on its own but there are just too many things to pay attention to.
Thank you. {nl} It really helps lifting our spirits.
With your abilities, I have one more favor to ask. {nl} Can you help us drive out the Chupacabras in the supplies camp too?
The Miners' Village is a problem but out situation here is not so good either. {nl}We have to prepare some measures before the number of  monsters increase even more..
Are you done already? {nl} No one has completed as fast before.
I'm in the mission to find out why the monsters in the East woords suddenly increased. {nl}Also, I act as the intermediate in supplying the Miner's Village. {nl}
Other knight is out in the Miner's Village but.. {nl} To be honest, It would have ended sooner if it was Sir Aras but the battle is taking longer than expected.
Since you're going to help, please get rid of the Giant Gray Chupacabras too. {nl}They are the culprits stealing our supplies.
Giant Gray Chupacabras appear when you kill normal chupacabras. {nl} Well then, thanks for your help.
Thank you. {nl} Now we can finally get to work easily.
Finding the cause of the monsters is important, {nl} but I'm more worried supplies not making it to the Miners' Village.
The movement of weavers in the lower area of the stream seems suspicious . {nl} Just like they're trying to interfere with supplying the Miners' Village.
It's not a usual situation. {nl} But we might have to give up our current supplies and support ourselves until the next batch of supplies arrive.
Thank you. {nl} With you Helping us out like this, we will not be defeated.
The next mission is to find the cause of the monsters increasing. {nl} Popolions have a big appetitle so we may be able to find crucial clue.
Miners' Village is already in trouble and if the East Woods is in this situation, we can't assure the safety of Klaipeda . {nl}We can just hope that Klaipeda is doing well.
Operations officer
Were you sent by Aras? {nl} It's a piece of Vubbe clothing. Hmm... Is that so...
I think the Vubbes of the Miner's Village have made their way into the woods. {nl} Maybe that's the reason behind the sudden increase in monsters too. {nl}
I better ask Sir Aras to search for Vubbes in other areas too. {nl} In the meantime, please take a look at the upper side.
We haven't searched the upper side yet. {nl} Of course, we should be sending troops but I ask for your help as this is an urgent matter.
You saw the Vubbe fighter but missed it? {nl} We also got a report that the Vubbe fighter appeared in the area below. {nl}
First, talk to the search scout in the lower bridge of Bulvjes. {nl} This will become a tedious long term war if  we miss the Vubbe fighter.
So Vubbe Fighter was the reason behind the increase of monsters. {nl} Please find out how many Vubbe Fighters there are. {nl}
Under the circumstances, it makes sense that the monsters are controlled by Vubbe Fighter. {nl} But deep down, you just don't want to believe it.
Following your report, there is no more Vubbe Fighter in this woods. {nl}
Let's get rid of the Vubbe Fighter. {nl} The search scouts are on standby in Nudegi Felled Area
Supply Solider
We need Weaver Claws as a part of supplies to be sent to Miners' Village {nl}but we just don't have time to look for those. {nl} What do we do?
Actually, it doesn't make sense for the supply solider to get the supplies.  {nl}It should have come from Klaipeda.
Thank you. {nl} Unexpected help always feels good.
In fact, everything would have been fine if Pokubus weren't around. {nl} The Pokubus were running wild and that's why were weren't able to retrieve all the supplies.
I don't know why they suddenly prey on the supplies. {nl} Could something be commanding them?
Thank you. {nl} I envy your ability.
Eastern Woods Search Scout
Oh, it's you. {nl} I have heard from the operations officer. {nl}
Vubbe Fighter is hiding deep in the Nudegi Felled Area. {nl} We got the orders to kill but it may be safer to wait for additional troops.
I'm just a search scout but it was my first time to see the Vubbe Fighter so near.
Awesome. You got rid of it by yourself. {nl} Go ahead and report to sir Aras. He'll be very pleased.
You mean you really killed the Vubbe Fighter? {nl}Well then, now we can be relieved since the number of monsters will no longer grow.
Of course. As promised, I will grant your access to the Miners' Village. {nl} Please wait.
If you find any clues, let the Operations Officer in the northern area know about it.
I think the Miners' Village is not in a good situation. {nl}It's too late to move the troops so you go first to support the Miners' Village.
They have low IQ but these monsters build groups and live as a community. {nl} They used to appear only occasionally in the deeper areas of the mines... Could they be expanding their forces? {nl}
Whatever the reason is, Vubbes expanding their territory is a big problem. {nl} The monster that lose  territory to Vubbes will be forced to make their way into our base.
It's a single road from here on so you'll be able to find the people easily. {nl}
Oh, let me give you some helpful information in return to your kind act for our village. {nl} The evidence of salvation that the Revelators are looking for can be found in the Closed Area.
One thing, there's something that keeps bothering me. {nl} A vague feeling of something alien.
Miner
Thank you for saving me. {nl} The revelator has come to save us. It's like a dream. {nl}
The Closed Area? {nl} If you insist to get in..  Gather the mysterious stones the Vubbes have. {nl} The walls just open when you touch the crystal clogged wall with it.
I'm collecting the supplies to be sent to the Miners Village. {nl} The monsters stole it all. {nl}
But supply box also contains dangerous explosives and collecting them is not an easy task.
They couldn't have gone far. {nl}It would have been better it exploded on their way.
I knew you would. {nl} One more thing, the ground of the Closed Area is weak so the entrance have been blocked for a long time. {nl}
The kidnapped people are veteran miners so they may know how to get in. {nl} Well then, may be blessings of Goddess be with you.
It wasn't long ago. {nl} I felt a strange power while performing various experiments in the Closed Area. {nl}It was different from the mana that we know but it was very warm. {nl}
But the force that did not allow me to approach it as if it had an owner already. {nl} A few days after the incident, the bishop dreamed about the evidence of salvation. {nl}
Perhaps the evidence of salvation is the force I felt .. {nl} That's what I think.
All I see are monsters and we're out of supplies. {nl}I'm also curious how the battle situation is in Miners' Village.
Until I'm assigned a new task, I'm thinking of going back to my duties as a search scout. {nl} Observing the monsters, you know.
The Miners' Village is under battle and entrance is prohibited for civilians. {nl}Remember that we can't guarantee your safety if you do not get my permission.
You have to cheer up.{nl} Even sir Aras is holding on.
Goddess Zemyna overlooks the earth. {nl}There are rumors that the Goddess has abandoned us but that's nonsense. {nl}Her statue still shines beautifully when you pray to it.
Vubbes suddenly came pouring in from outside of the Siaulai Woods. {nl} That's why the Mining Village located in the middle of it turned to a battlefield. {nl}

That's why I can't permit entrance to the Miners Village for safety reasons. {nl} Of course it will be a different story if your skill are good enough to ensure your safety even without the protection of guards.
Gosh, it could have been really dangerous. {nl} That huge thing was hiding so well.
It's very important to study monsters at times like this. {nl}It's like weather forecasts where you try to find out the cause and see what would happen.
I'm sure the leaf bugs in Uoros farm stole it. {nl}They did steal from us once before.
Send my regards to the Guard Captain when you meet him.
Then, in order to test if your skills are good enough to enter the Miners Village.. {nl} I need you to help us solve a problem we have. {nl}
First, take back the farm from the Pokubus. {nl} I believe this would be a fairly easy task
There seems to be a gap in the rock where you can insert something.
Let's search the Bulvjes farm first. {nl}But don't chase them or something as it can be dangerous.
It makes me wonder if you're an envoy of the Goddess. {nl} Anyway, supplies camp is located further below the farm.
Vubbes are emerging inside the Mine Gallery so be sure to stay together in groups of 5.
Equipment  Merchant
Even at times like this, I struggle to find the best items I can. You can't go easy in terms of dealing with your customers.
Monsters attack and steal from people who buy items from me. I think they know can tell which items are good. I feel sorry for those who were attacked but it also proves that the items are worth it.
The monsters never raided into Klaipeda but with sir Uska gone, it's hard to be at ease. You have you watch out for yourself at times like this.
I want to travel with a single weapon in hand like an adventurer.. But I guess that's hard..
If you listen to the soldiers, they use terms only they can understand and make it sound difficult. And when I ask a friend soldier, it's not like they are talking about anything important.
Be cautious of people who sell weapons from monsters without permit. They scam you to buy useless things or sell at ridiculously high prices.
Item Merchant
It's the little things you miss out that makes you regret when you travel. Better to buy enough of it when you can.
I feel sorry for those who were injured. Can't we get along with the monsters?
I'd rather want to stay safe and at peace even if the sales would be lower rather than sales going up because of people worrying when the monsters would attack.
I sell things that people need but I sometimes think it would have been better if i was a healer because you can be closer to the explorers to help them.
I hear strange howling from a distance. Could it be the sound of the monstesr?
People say I'm weird and I talk too much but i don't mind. Even if I'm really weird like they say, that doesn't mean even the items I sell are also weird.
Blacksmith
Hello. {nl} I can help you repair items but I can't craft new ones because I don't have the materials.  {nl} Go on and choose from whatever is available.
Klaipeda resident
It's true we're in tough times but everyone looking after the soldiers only.
Aside from anything else, I want to eat till i'm full. {nl} You need to eat to have strength.
Why have the Goddess disappeared? {nl} Everyone is looking for where they've gone but no one is asking why they disappeared.
I can't eat, wear, or rest freely because of those monsters. {nl} In the old days, we used gather herbs or pick fruits in Siaulai Forest you know.
Everyone is talking about the war wherever you go. {nl} Like who and how much people are hurt or who's assigned to where. {nl} All the stories about the war makes me sick!
I heard they will send soldiers who aren't even trained into the nest of monsters. {nl} It might be better to gather the old people and make them soldiers.
My life is just a repetition of worries and anger. {nl} The Goddess should return soon.
There are suddenly many people who dreamed about the revelation. {nl} Could it be a sign of something about to happen again? {nl}
Bishop of Klaipeda also dreamed about the Goddess. {nl} Could it be the same dream with the Revelators?
Mother of Soldier
)} My son had enlisted to the Army. {nl} He said who would if not him at such difficult times like this.
)} Monster are growing and the forest is too chaotic for people to live in. {nl} At least, Klaipeda is safe.
)} At least Klaipeda is safe but other cities are in chaos? {nl} Well, putting aside the capital, Fedimian has totally collapsed except for the Sacred Area.
)} It's a good thing that my son accomplished his dream of becoming a solder.. {nl} But the monsters are rising and I'm worried he might get hurt.
)} Maybe Klaipeda is where the Goddess has bestowed her blessings. {nl} I hope the blessings would also reach my son who enlisted in the army.
)} My husband used to be a miner and how relieved I am that he isn't anymore. {nl} It would be too dangerous if the monsters raid at times like this isn't it?
)} Many refugees came from the fallen town. {nl} Our food supplies are also running short but we still have to help each other.
I may not bring in the items with best quality but isn't having all the items necessary a skill of its own? Gotta work hard to get through tough times.
I think the best weapons and armors are the ones that you get used to over a long period time. In order to do so, you must start first by buying good items.
